When placing JavaScript in a custom field, <script> tags are removed and appended to the end of the Create Issue dialog when the dialog is first opened.

{code}
A.unconfigurableForm.render().done(function(E, D) {
    B.resolveWith(A, [A.$element, D]);
    A.$element.append(D) // D is all <script> elements, A.$element is dialog
})
{code}

However, no similar <script> append occurs after script removal when switching between projects or issue types.  This means that if our custom field (with javascript) is not in the Project or Issue Type initially loaded when the Create Issue dialog is rendered, it will not be executed.

